00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:49,240
<i>Here in the kingdom of Malaria,</i>

9
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:54,320
<i>every day's forecast is rainy
with a 100% chance of horror.</i>

10
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:56,960
<i>It wasn't always like this, though.</i>

11
00:00:57,640 --> 00:01:00,320
<i>Years ago, Malaria was
a sunny land of farmers.</i>

12
00:01:00,440 --> 00:01:03,680
<i>Until the mysterious storm clouds
rolled in and never left.</i>

13
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:09,280
<i>They killed our crops,
and our people became poor.</i>

14
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:11,040
<i>And that's when King Malbert...</i>

15
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:13,360
<i>thought up a new way
for us to make money,</i>

16
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:15,240
<i>Evil Inventions.</i>

17
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:18,240
<i>The kind that crush you, kill you,
bring you back to life,</i>

18
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:20,720
<i>then kill you again,
way worse.</i>

19
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:23,160
<i>We invent them, and the world
pays us not to unleash them.</i>

20
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:27,200
<i>Oh, It's a great gig, especially
if you're an Evil Scientist.</i>

21
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:30,280
<i>Fame, fortune,
a rent-free castle in the hills.</i>

22
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:32,520
<i>They get it all.
They're the top of the heap.</i>

23
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,520
Igor! Pull the switch!

24
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:39,000
Yes, Master!

25
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:42,960
<i>And the bottom of the heap?
Those are the poor slobs like me,</i>

26
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:46,040
<i>born with a hunch on our back, Igors.</i>

27
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:48,440
<i>Actually, that Igor's not me.</i>

28
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:53,000
Igor! Pull the switch!

29
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:55,240
Yes, Master!

30
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:57,360
<i>No, no, no,
that's not me, either.</i>

31
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:04,240
<i>That's me. See?
I look nothing like those other guys,</i>

32
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:05,720
<i>much better-looking.</i>

33
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:09,880
<i>Anyway, all Igors are forced
to serve Evil Scientists.</i>

34
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:13,160
<i>Our life is a permanent graveyard shift.</i>

35
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:15,520
<i>But I never wanted to be an Igor.</i>

36
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:19,200
<i>I always wanted to be
an Evil Scientist.</i>

37
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:23,120
<i>Unfortunately, the hunch on my
back was a one-way ticket</i>

38
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,560
<i>to Igor School.</i>

39
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:29,600
<i>I majored in Talking With a Slur
and graduated with a Yes Masters Degree.</i>

40
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:32,240
<i>Then, it was off to find a job.</i>

41
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:36,320
Hi, I'm here about the "Igor Wanted" ad.
My name's Igor.

42
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:38,680
Well, of course it is.
I've got a hunch on my back.

43
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,600
What's my name gonna be? Kevin?

44
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,880
<i>They didn't
appreciate my creative style.</i>

45
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:51,240
<i>But eventually, I landed a job
for Dr. Glickenstein.</i>

46
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:53,720
Pull the switch!

47
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,080
<i>Not the smartest scientist.</i>

48
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:59,000
<i>His last invention was an Evil Lasagna.</i>

49
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:01,720
<i>It didn't kill anyone.
And it actually tasted pretty good.</i>

50
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,880
Igor!

51
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,960
<i>Igors aren't allowed to invent,</i>

52
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:09,800
<i>but I still manage to work
on my own inventions in secret.</i>

53
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:11,600
<i>And this new one is gonna be
the one that proves</i>

54
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:15,400
<i>that I'm the biggest Evil Genius
of them all, and not just another...</i>

55
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,080
Igor!

56
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:24,000
<i>Once they see what I can do,
I'll have a whole new life,</i>

57
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:27,480
<i>and I'll never have to answer
to another master again.</i>

58
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,360
Sorry Master.
What did you say?

59
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,760
Oh! I mean...

60
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:35,400
Sorry, Master.
I was in the bathroom.

61
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:39,600
Had a bat stuck in the belfry,
if you know what I mean, Master.

62
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,600
I don't want to hear your
toilet memoirs, you cretin!

63
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:45,960
I give you five minutes a week
to take care of your business.

64
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:48,520
I'm not running a resort here!

65
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:51,720
Now get over there and...

66
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,440
Pull the switch!

67
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:55,680
Yes, Master!

68
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,640
Yes! Yes!

69
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,880
Yes!

70
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:20,880
Who's the failure now, Mother?

71
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:33,160
Mummy, Mummy, you were right!

72
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,880
I was never meant to be a scientist.

73
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:39,120
I should have been a plumber like you!

74
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,280
That was the first time
he was right all day.

75
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:46,480
You! Go find me a 16-gigawatt
temporal transducer!

76
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:50,680
Excuse me, Master, are you sure
you don't mean 21-gigawatt?

77
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,800
You're correcting me?

78
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,320
Strike!

79
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,400
I should do more improv.

80
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,720
My hunch.

81
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:06,120
Oh, there she goes. Much better.

82
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,160
<i>Good evening, friends!</i>

83
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:11,480
<i>That's Scamper,
one of my most successful inventions.</i>

84
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,240
<i>I made him immortal.</i>

85
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:22,600
<i>Which is kind of a hassle for him,
since he doesn't want to live.</i>

86
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:25,440
Will nothing end this vicious cycle?

87
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,920
<i>I also made him talk.</i>

88
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,560
<i>Which is a hassle for me,
since he never shuts up.</i>

89
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,720
No fair!

90
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:33,680
You wasted your immortality formula
on the wrong guy, Igor.

91
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:36,040
<i>That's Brain, one
of my other inventions.</i>

92
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:38,480
<i>Legend has it when the smartest
man in the world died,</i>

93
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,440
<i>they put his brain in a jar.</i>

94
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:42,320
<i>This is not that brain.</i>

95
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:45,320
I wanna live forever!
I got plans! And dreams!

96
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:47,480
I got a squeaky wheel!
Was that me?

97
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,520
Really, Brain?

98
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:51,280
You want to be trapped in an
endless existential nightmare,

99
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,360
forced to keep living,

100
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:54,400
even though life is meaningless

101
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,720
and nothing matters?

102
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:57,120
Possibly.

103
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,920
What exactly did you say?

104
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:02,640
Too bad he wasted his intelligence
formula on me, too, Brain.

105
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:04,880
Or should I say "Brian"?

106
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:07,280
Hey! I was in a hurry!

107
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:09,480
Stupid permanent marker.

108
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,520
Enough.

109
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:11,960
The Evil Science Fair is in a week,

110
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:14,440
and Glickenstein is gonna lose again.

111
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:17,160
Okay, I get it.
You want me to fix his invention.

112
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:21,280
Now I'll just need a screwdriver,
some nails and my bag of marbles.

113
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,800
Don't touch his invention, Brain.

114
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:25,640
Fine! You don't want the
benefit of my brain power?

115
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:27,160
Then, farewell, Igor.

116
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:31,280
Like a gentle fawn,
I shall leave this meadow.

117
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,720
On second thought
maybe I'll stick around,

118
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:44,920
so I can watch Mr. Smarty-hunch

119
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,680
fix Glickenstein's invention.

120
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,960
I could! But you know
what would happen if I did!

121
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:52,840
The same thing he'd do if he
found out I invented you two.

122
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,360
He'd recycle me.

123
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:57,040
Can you imagine being chopped up
and used for body parts

124
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,600
and God knows what else?

125
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,880
Horrible.

126
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,280
Dang it!
Still here.

127
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,200
If I had my shot,

128
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:14,480
I could be one of the greatest
Evil Scientists Malaria has ever seen.

129
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:17,480
They'd all cheer my name

130
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:20,840
just like they do for the
great Dr. Schadenfreude!

131
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:41,600
And now your
master of disaster, the chief of grief,

132
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,240
a man who needs no introduction,

133
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:45,960
but who will brutally
torture me if he doesn't get one,

134
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:49,280
Dr. Schadenfreude!

135
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:53,160
Thank you thank you.
You're too kind

136
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:54,680
And I'm not.

137
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:59,200
But I want to welcome you all to my
annual pre-Evil Science Fair party.

138
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:00,520
My girlfriend Jaclyn.

139
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:02,560
You know, she may seem like

140
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:04,840
a shallow, conniving wretch...

141
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:08,720
That's all I got.
That pretty much sums her up.

142
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:15,920
A toast to the undefeated winner
of 17 Evil Science Fairs

143
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:19,000
and the greatest Evil
Genius in the world.

144
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:23,080
Bow for the King!

145
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,000
"The greatest Evil
Genius in the world. "

146
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:31,520
I remember when people
used to call me that.

147
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:35,160
Back when the clouds destroyed
our peaceful land of farmers,

148
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:39,000
and my plan to blackmail
the world saved us all

149
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:43,880
Yes, as you've told us all
over and over and over.

150
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,480
Yeah, well, here's more.

151
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:49,560
Did you know that years ago,
Schoddy's family name was Poekelmacher?

152
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:52,880
His family were pickle-makers.

153
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:58,160
So, what's your Evil Invention
this year, Doctor, kosher or dill?

154
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:04,200
I want to shove a pickle
right where the sun don't shine.

155
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:06,440
You mean Malaria, Master?

156
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:11,080
No matter how many
Evil Science Fairs I win,

157
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:14,000
I always have to bow
down to that idiot.

158
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:16,120
I will never get the respect he gets!

159
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:20,240
Respect? Respect isn't gonna
keep me in baby-seal boots.

160
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:24,000
You just need to keep on winning

161
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:27,440
Well, that is spoken
like a true worthless leech,

162
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:32,120
who, by the way still has not helped
me steal this year's winning invention.

163
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:34,280
You know, maybe if you
were a real scientist,

164
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:36,520
you wouldn't need
me to help you cheat every year.

165
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:41,800
Your whole lab is fake,

166
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:43,440
just like you.

167
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:50,000
And maybe I should throw you
back in the gutter where I found you!

168
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:53,400
You're one to talk,
Dr. Schadenfraude!

169
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,680
You don't have the guts.

170
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:09,680
Is Daddy still mad at me?

171
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:11,600
No.

172
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,480
But you and your friend Heidi

173
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,480
still have a little job to do.

174
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,960
Oh, we're trying.

175
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:20,440
Well, try a little bit harder!

176
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:23,200
Because this year,

177
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:25,160
I won't stop at just winning
the Evil Science Fair.

178
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:29,080
I'm gonna unleash my winning invention

179
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:32,840
on the King's smug little face,

180
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:36,120
and then he'll be the one
groveling at my feet!

181
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,320
Hi there.

182
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:45,320
Look, it's your
little girlfriend, Heidi.

183
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:46,600
You take a cocoa break,

184
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,520
and I'll guard your plans
for your new invention.

185
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,280
No, wait! You'll spill on my plans.

186
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,960
Heidi, you're not careful enough!

187
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:55,000
You're so sloppy sometimes.

188
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:56,840
Oh, poopshkin.

189
00:10:56,960 --> 00:11:01,000
I went to the evil bookstore
and got you an inspirational poster.

190
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,840
It's a little kitten!

191
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:07,920
To remind you to always take time
in your day for a little torture.

192
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,040
My transducer!

193
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:14,600
Time to go.
I have no time for cocoa or kittens!

194
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:16,320
I have to work on my plans
alone and in secret.

195
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:19,480
In other words, bon voyage.

196
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:23,400
Who doesn't like tortured kittens?

197
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:25,760
I...
I like kittens.

198
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:28,840
I don't like dirty little hunchpeople.

199
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:31,640
Great, Schadenfreude's gonna kil me.

200
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:36,320
<i>And why are there two transducers?</i>

201
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:40,760
Master, the 21-gigawatt
might be somewhat safer, I think.

202
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:43,800
Think? Igors don't think.

203
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:46,760
I'm using the 16-gigawatt, you fool!

204
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:50,480
Now get over there and pull the switch!

205
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,760
What are you waiting for?

206
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:57,280
Yes, Master!

207
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:02,720
Yes! Yes!

208
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,960
Yes!

209
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:11,160
I told you the 16 would work, you Igor.

210
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:15,880
Behold my rocket ship!

211
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:19,160
Born to stream through the world,

212
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:22,520
unleashing pain and misery on everyone.

213
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:25,720
I named her after you, Mother.

214
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:31,840
Now to take the old
cow for a test drive.

215
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,600
No, Master!
The rocket is going to...

216
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,720
Uh... Yeah that.

217
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,000
Finally.

218
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:49,440
Now I can throw out that rug
in the foyer. That thing is hideous.

219
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:51,520
We were all thinking it.
I just said it.

220
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:54,320
Oh, no, who's that?
What am I gonna do?

221
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:56,960
Relax, this is Glickenstein's castle.

222
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:59,080
And he doesn't have
to open that door for anyone.

223
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:00,760
Open for the King!

224
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,160
Except for the King.
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

225
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:04,960
He's here to see Glickenstein!
What do I tell him?

226
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,280
Tell him the truth.
And if he kills us,

227
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,760
I'll come back
and give you a beautiful funeral.

228
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:11,360
Right, right. The truth,
that's a good option. Right, right.

229
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:15,040
Glicky!
Glicky, my boy.

230
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:16,480
Where's Glicky?

231
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,760
Your Highness, he's gone.

232
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:20,960
Curse it, I need to see his invention.

233
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:22,600
Schadenfreude is getting too popular.

234
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:24,160
The people might make him king.

235
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:25,520
Someone has to beat him this year,

236
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:27,720
with an invention more evil than his.

237
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:30,440
Someone who can snatch
Schadenfreude's number one position

238
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,600
and rub his face in number two!

239
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:33,680
Ew...

240
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:37,000
Your Highness,
Dr. Glickenstein is...

241
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:39,040
