I think we better open it.

740
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:50,240
It's a new label for your jar.

741
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:53,400
And Brain is spelled right!

742
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:55,560
It is, right?

743
00:41:55,680 --> 00:41:57,680
You shouldn't really worry
about labels, though,

744
00:41:57,800 --> 00:42:00,000
because you may be a brain,
but you have heart.

745
00:42:01,200 --> 00:42:03,240
And in some ways,
that's more important.

746
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:06,040
Heart? I'd kill for a pair of feet.

747
00:42:07,320 --> 00:42:10,960
Open yours, Scamper.
It s a prehistoric evergreen.

748
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:13,480
They live forever.
I just want to make sure

749
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:15,840
that if anything
ever happens to the three of us,

750
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:17,080
you always have company.

751
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:20,080
Great. I must be allergic to it.

752
00:42:20,200 --> 00:42:23,640
With any luck, it'll kill me
with its dinosaur-era toxins.

753
00:42:24,640 --> 00:42:26,600
Can we move on to Igor now?

754
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:30,360
No one's ever given me a gift before.

755
00:42:30,480 --> 00:42:33,160
It's something no
director can be without.

756
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:35,520
A beret!

757
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:39,160
Voil!

758
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:40,480
That's French for,

759
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:43,200
"Please stop pelting me and
my ridiculous hat with rocks. "

760
00:42:43,320 --> 00:42:45,720
Hey, Igor where's our gift for Eva?

761
00:42:46,120 --> 00:42:47,040
Our gift?

762
00:42:47,160 --> 00:42:48,960
Oh! You guys didn't.

763
00:42:49,080 --> 00:42:50,200
We did.

764
00:42:51,080 --> 00:42:53,000
Where'd you put it, Igor?

765
00:42:53,160 --> 00:42:55,960
It s in the other room.

766
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:01,880
Gift, gift, gift, gift.

767
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:10,520
Eva. Well, we got you this.

768
00:43:11,760 --> 00:43:13,240
It's a necklace.

769
