It's the most beautiful
thing I've ever seen!

770
00:43:25,240 --> 00:43:26,720
Igor, can you...

771
00:43:26,840 --> 00:43:28,880
I would do it myself,
but I am all thumbs.

772
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:32,200
Yeah, I'm sorry about that.
I got the thumbs on sale.

773
00:43:33,120 --> 00:43:34,240
I'm never gonna take this off.

774
00:43:34,360 --> 00:43:37,600
That way all of you will be
close to my heart forever.

775
00:43:39,680 --> 00:43:43,040
I need to go write this down
in my sense-memory journal!

776
00:43:43,360 --> 00:43:45,240
Oh, where did I put my glitter pen?

777
00:43:47,520 --> 00:43:49,680
See, this is the kind of
moment that'd be tough

778
00:43:49,800 --> 00:43:52,840
for someone who wasn't meant
to be an Evil Scientist.

779
00:43:52,960 --> 00:43:56,440
Somebody who'd go all soft
and want to tell her the truth.

780
00:43:57,720 --> 00:44:00,120
But lucky for us, I'm evil, right?

781
00:44:00,240 --> 00:44:01,880
Yeah. Lucky us.

782
00:44:02,880 --> 00:44:04,520
I don't feel lucky.

783
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:17,200
So we stay on track,
'cause we're almost there,

784
00:44:17,320 --> 00:44:20,000
and I just don't let
her get into my head.

785
00:44:25,240 --> 00:44:27,160
It s so hard being a little hunchback.

786
00:44:27,280 --> 00:44:28,360
Heidi!

787
00:44:28,480 --> 00:44:31,240
Dr. Glickenstein is under the rug.
I mean, under the weather.

788
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:33,240
I didn't come to see him.

789
00:44:33,840 --> 00:44:35,960
I came to see you.

790
00:44:36,720 --> 00:44:37,720
Me?

791
00:44:44,320 --> 00:44:48,080
By the way, an Igor came by today

792
00:44:48,200 --> 00:44:50,840
and asked me to
hands-deliver this to you.

793
00:44:51,320 --> 00:44:53,080
And these are my hands.

794
00:44:54,160 --> 00:44:55,080
What? What is it?

795
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:57,000
<i>Ja, I haven't any idea.</i>

796
00:44:57,120 --> 00:44:58,640
"Wish You Weren't There. "

797
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:07,000
Oh, excellent, wonderful.

798
00:45:07,360 --> 00:45:08,920
You got my card.

799
00:45:12,080 --> 00:45:13,000
Is everything okay?

800
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:15,040
I heard a strange noise.

801
00:45:15,160 --> 00:45:16,080
Ooh!

802
00:45:16,200 --> 00:45:18,440
Oh, I wasn't at the door
listening to you and Igor.

803
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:19,800
I just...

804
00:45:20,800 --> 00:45:23,720
Hi! We haven't met. I'm Eva.

805
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:28,160
Oh you're upset, aren't you?

806
00:45:28,280 --> 00:45:31,080
"Who is this strange woman
living with Igor," right?

807
00:45:31,200 --> 00:45:33,720
Well, believe me,
Igor and I are just friends.

808
00:45:33,840 --> 00:45:36,360
As his girlfriend you have
nothing to worry about.

809
00:45:36,480 --> 00:45:38,040
I'm not his girlfriend.

810
00:45:38,160 --> 00:45:39,320
You're not?

811
00:45:39,440 --> 00:45:41,480
But the way he looks at you...

812
00:45:42,080 --> 00:45:43,400
He never looks at me that way.

813
00:45:43,520 --> 00:45:45,480
Maybe some men like girls

814
00:45:45,600 --> 00:45:49,240
who don't look like they've
been put together at the junkyard.

815
00:45:50,880 --> 00:45:51,880
Right.

816
00:45:52,000 --> 00:45:54,600
You have a very ugly face.

817
00:45:56,360 --> 00:45:59,200
Well, I have to go
get some rest for my audit on tomorrow.

818
00:45:59,360 --> 00:46:00,560
It was nice meeting you.

819
00:46:00,680 --> 00:46:01,640
Oh.

820
00:46:02,800 --> 00:46:03,960
Whoops!

821
00:46:05,800 --> 00:46:07,000
Audit on?

822
00:46:12,320 --> 00:46:14,840
So, how's your cocktail, Igor?

823
00:46:14,960 --> 00:46:16,840
Is it nice? You like t?

824
00:46:16,960 --> 00:46:19,880
Is it coconut-ty?
Coconut-ty enough?

825
00:46:20,000 --> 00:46:23,000
Wait! You should be sipping in style!

826
00:46:23,520 --> 00:46:25,560
Igor Krazy Straw!
Right now.

827
00:46:28,560 --> 00:46:31,240
Small trumpet. Isn't that better?
Doesn't that taste better?

828
00:46:31,360 --> 00:46:32,280
Excuse me, sir, but why...

829
00:46:33,880 --> 00:46:35,600
I mean, why am I here?

830
00:46:35,720 --> 00:46:37,480
You can drop that slur around me.

831
00:46:37,600 --> 00:46:40,560
I don't even make my Igors talk
that way. Isn't that right, Igor?

832
00:46:40,680 --> 00:46:44,200
Oh, that's right, Master.

833
00:46:44,320 --> 00:46:45,960
How many times do I have to tell you?

834
00:46:46,080 --> 00:46:48,440
Call me Frederick.
Okay? That's my name.

835
00:46:48,560 --> 00:46:50,360
Okay. Frederick!

836
00:46:51,080 --> 00:46:53,640
I have to get back.
Dr. Glickenstein will be missing me.

837
00:46:53,760 --> 00:46:57,920
Somehow, I think he's missing
more than his right-hand man.

838
00:46:59,080 --> 00:47:03,800
Look, Iggy baby I know all about
Glickenstein and his deadness.

839
00:47:04,960 --> 00:47:07,120
I also know about your monster.

840
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:09,440
I m gonna guess your plan.

841
00:47:09,560 --> 00:47:11,160
You win the Evil Science Fair,

842
00:47:11,240 --> 00:47:13,640
and then everyone looks
past the hunch thing,

843
00:47:13,760 --> 00:47:15,560
and they accept you for the real you.

844
00:47:15,680 --> 00:47:18,200
You grab the girl of your dreams
and you cha-cha-cha your way

845
00:47:18,320 --> 00:47:19,360
to a happy ending.

846
00:47:19,480 --> 00:47:20,480
Am I close on this?

847
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:21,960
No, not entirely.

848
00:47:23,440 --> 00:47:24,760
I don't know how to cha-cha.

849
00:47:25,480 --> 00:47:27,840
We're a lot alike, Igor.

850
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:29,920
I want to be more as well,

851
00:47:30,040 --> 00:47:32,360
but society, it won't let me.
It stops me.

852
00:47:32,480 --> 00:47:33,480
So, this is my plan:

853
00:47:33,600 --> 00:47:36,680
I enter Evil Science Fair
with your monster and then I win.

854
00:47:36,800 --> 00:47:38,840
I turn the monster on the King.

855
00:47:38,960 --> 00:47:42,360
Ding dong, the King is dead,
long live the new king, me!

856
00:47:44,360 --> 00:47:49,800
And then you come in as Malaria's
new Evil Scientist Dr. Igor.

857
00:47:50,480 --> 00:47:51,960
So what do you say to
that? Is that nice?

858
00:47:52,080 --> 00:47:52,840
Is that really nice?

859
00:47:52,880 --> 00:47:54,640
You want to overthrow the King?

860
00:47:54,760 --> 00:47:57,040
I thought you wanted
to be an Evil Scientist.

861
00:47:57,160 --> 00:47:58,080
I do. But...

862
00:47:58,200 --> 00:47:59,800
Stop thinking like an Igor!

863
00:47:59,920 --> 00:48:03,080
Evil Scientists do not let
anyone stand in their way.

864
00:48:03,760 --> 00:48:05,880
Yes. I know. They step
on people to get ahead.

865
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:07,120
Exactly!

866
00:48:08,000 --> 00:48:08,960
She'll never do it.

867
00:48:09,080 --> 00:48:09,960
She?

868
00:48:10,080 --> 00:48:11,240
The monster.
She isn't evil.

869
00:48:11,360 --> 00:48:13,800
Something went wrong and her
Evil Bone was never activated.

870
00:48:13,920 --> 00:48:17,000
So how do we get this Evil Bone
up and running, huh?

871
00:48:17,120 --> 00:48:20,880
We kick it, we slap it,
we take it to the movies, call it Irene?

872
00:48:21,400 --> 00:48:22,680
She needs to commit an evil act,

873
00:48:22,800 --> 00:48:24,360
but since she's not evil, she won't.

874
00:48:26,520 --> 00:48:27,880
Well, your troubles are over then,

875
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:31,320
because I can get a woman
to do absolutely anything.

876
00:48:31,880 --> 00:48:32,840
I don't know.

877
00:48:32,960 --> 00:48:36,240
Don't tell me that you have
feelings for this thing?

878
00:48:36,360 --> 00:48:37,680
- No.
- Good,

879
00:48:38,400 --> 00:48:40,640
because that would be pathetic.

880
00:48:41,520 --> 00:48:45,920
I can give you everything
you have ever wanted.

881
00:48:46,400 --> 00:48:47,400
I think I need to go.

882
00:48:47,520 --> 00:48:49,920
Look, the Evil Science Fair
is in a few hours.

883
00:48:50,040 --> 00:48:52,800
You're either with me or against me.

884
00:48:52,920 --> 00:48:55,000
Yes or no?

885
00:48:58,600 --> 00:49:00,160
I take that as a no.

886
00:49:00,320 --> 00:49:02,840
What are you going to do now, smart guy?

887
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:19,200
Oh!

888
00:49:22,280 --> 00:49:23,320
No!

889
00:49:25,120 --> 00:49:26,640
Frederick!

890
00:49:28,320 --> 00:49:30,040
Frederick! Why are you swimming?

891
00:49:30,160 --> 00:49:31,720
You just ate 10 minutes ago.

892
00:49:31,840 --> 00:49:33,480
Get off of me, you buffoon!

893
00:50:02,760 --> 00:50:04,480
Okay,
we finished your costume.

894
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:06,760
I just hope it's cinched
enough at the waist.

895
00:50:06,880 --> 00:50:09,000
Obviously, if I had more time,
I would have made it flare out

896
00:50:09,120 --> 00:50:10,320
a little bit more over the knees.

897
00:50:10,440 --> 00:50:13,480
Stop touching it, Brain,
I'm creating a look here.

898
00:50:14,440 --> 00:50:17,440
You guys are my friends.
So, you'll tell me the truth, right?

899
00:50:17,560 --> 00:50:19,080
Yeah, sure.

900
00:50:20,040 --> 00:50:22,360
Do you think I'm pretty?

901
00:50:24,880 --> 00:50:28,680
Brain, get me a tub of eye-liner,
a pound of lipstick,

902
00:50:28,800 --> 00:50:32,360
and if all else fails,
the severed head of a supermodel.

903
00:50:32,480 --> 00:50:35,200
Okay, the Jacuzzi is not a bathroom.

904
00:50:35,280 --> 00:50:36,040
I know that now.

905
00:50:37,240 --> 00:50:39,760
Please, please take your own
sweet time! I'm loving it here!

906
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:41,280
Oh, really?

907
00:50:41,400 --> 00:50:43,120
Well, then maybe you
should stay down there

908
00:50:43,240 --> 00:50:45,640
with your Igor, poopshkin!

909
00:50:45,760 --> 00:50:47,880
You know something?
He's a good listener,

910
00:50:48,000 --> 00:50:51,840
he's got soft hands, and unlike you,
he sometimes shaves his legs!

911
00:51:00,960 --> 00:51:04,320
Wait.
No kissing Heidi.

912
00:51:06,880 --> 00:51:09,480
Or do you like me better as Heidi?

913
00:51:09,640 --> 00:51:12,360
Hmm. Jaclyn, Heidi, Jaclyn, Heidi.

914
00:51:13,680 --> 00:51:14,760
It would be really swell

915
00:51:14,880 --> 00:51:17,320
if you didn't go
psycho-girlfriend on me right now.

916
00:51:17,440 --> 00:51:19,240
I'm not psycho!

917
00:51:19,360 --> 00:51:20,320
Obviously not.

918
00:51:20,440 --> 00:51:25,480
How would you feel if every day
you had to be 13 different people?

919
00:51:25,600 --> 00:51:28,080
I'm Jaclyn, your girlfriend.

920
00:51:30,720 --> 00:51:33,480
Then I'm Dr. Nachtmahrs girlfriend.

921
00:51:34,400 --> 00:51:36,840
Then I'm Dr. Groaner's girlfriend.

922
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:38,480
All for you!

923
00:51:38,600 --> 00:51:41,800
To help you steal
inventions year after year.

924
00:51:41,920 --> 00:51:45,960
And I still say those stolen pills
were the best invention yet.

925
00:51:46,080 --> 00:51:48,800
Well, this time they really paid off.

926
00:51:48,920 --> 00:51:51,640
Guess what Mommy found out
about our favorite little monster?

927
00:51:51,760 --> 00:51:53,160
Or should I say actress?

928
00:51:53,280 --> 00:51:54,200
Oh.

929
00:51:57,040 --> 00:51:58,120
Eva.

930
00:52:02,240 --> 00:52:04,360
Eva, Eva!

931
00:52:08,920 --> 00:52:12,440
Just breathe. Okay.
Center yourself on the body.

932
00:52:19,880 --> 00:52:22,680
I'm ready for my close-up, Mr. Director.

933
00:52:29,400 --> 00:52:32,840
Oh, no, this isn't happening.
Act graceful. Act graceful.

934
00:52:32,960 --> 00:52:33,960
Keep smiling.

935
00:52:39,680 --> 00:52:41,000
Too close?

936
00:52:41,520 --> 00:52:44,480
No. Eva, you look...
You look beautiful.

937
00:52:45,240 --> 00:52:46,800
Oh this is such a clich,

938
00:52:46,920 --> 00:52:50,160
the leading lady falling
for her director.

939
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:53,160
Well, you're not used to high heels

940
00:52:54,760 --> 00:52:56,240
Oh, you mean...

941
00:52:56,840 --> 00:52:58,480
Our work here is done.

942
00:52:58,600 --> 00:52:59,720
Our work?

943
00:52:59,840 --> 00:53:02,880
You spent the entire time
playing with a piece of ribbon.

944
00:53:07,600 --> 00:53:10,920
Eva, about the audition, I think
I've given you the wrong direction.

945
00:53:11,040 --> 00:53:13,600
But I feel so prepared.

946
00:53:13,720 --> 00:53:17,800
No, I've been trying to make you
play a role that you're not right for.

947
00:53:17,920 --> 00:53:18,800
What?

948
00:53:18,920 --> 00:53:20,000
I have to tell you the truth.

949
00:53:22,960 --> 00:53:25,520
He did.
I'll just be a minute.

950
00:53:27,960 --> 00:53:32,040
Oh, Igor. Ow!
My ankle.

951
00:53:32,160 --> 00:53:34,920
It twisted like the pretzel, Igor!

952
00:53:36,440 --> 00:53:37,880
Enchanting.

953
00:53:38,000 --> 00:53:40,480
Thank you. And who are you?

954
00:53:41,040 --> 00:53:45,880
Someone who does not want
your unique gifts to go to waste.

955
00:53:47,040 --> 00:53:48,480
Are you a talent agent?

956
00:53:48,880 --> 00:53:51,920
I was so deep down worried

957
00:53:52,040 --> 00:53:55,760
that when you opened the card
I thought I lost you forever.

958
00:53:55,880 --> 00:53:57,800
Heidi, I need to tell you something.

959
00:53:57,920 --> 00:53:59,320
I don't know what it is,

960
00:53:59,440 --> 00:54:02,480
but I fee like for the
first time in my life,

961
00:54:02,600 --> 00:54:05,640
I'm seeing a real Igor.

962
00:54:06,400 --> 00:54:09,160
And I think I'm in love with him.

963
00:54:13,160 --> 00:54:15,640
Wow, when it rains, it pours.

964
00:54:16,640 --> 00:54:17,560
No, no.

965
00:54:17,680 --> 00:54:20,120
Igor is a liar.
He does this...

966
00:54:20,240 --> 00:54:23,200
Igor would never lie to me.
Igor cares about me.

967
00:54:23,320 --> 00:54:25,320
Cares?
He doesn't care.

968
00:54:25,440 --> 00:54:28,240
Because he built you to be a weapon.

969
00:54:28,360 --> 00:54:30,720
No, no, no, you re wrong.

970
00:54:30,840 --> 00:54:33,120
He'll never look at you
and see a woman.

971
00:54:33,240 --> 00:54:36,040
All he will ever see is a monster.

972
00:54:36,160 --> 00:54:37,960
I don't believe you.

973
00:54:38,080 --> 00:54:39,880
Open your eyes.

974
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:43,520
Igor has someone else
in mind for your role.

975
00:54:43,640 --> 00:54:45,040
Heidi, no!

976
00:54:48,200 --> 00:54:49,840
There's nothing more for you here.

977
00:54:49,960 --> 00:54:53,960
Come with me.
I will make you a star.

978
00:55:12,480 --> 00:55:13,560
No.

979
00:55:15,240 --> 00:55:16,200
Oh!

980
00:55:16,320 --> 00:55:17,560
What's wrong?

981
00:55:17,680 --> 00:55:20,240
I can't believe I'm saying this,
but I've made someone else.

982
00:55:20,360 --> 00:55:21,320
